<CaseStudyLayout title="Supply Chain Workforce Benchmarking & Operating Model Assessment">
  <h1>Supply Chain Workforce Benchmarking & Operating Model Assessment</h1>

  <div class="cs-spec">
    <div><p class="k">Functional Topic</p><p class="v">Supply Chain Operating Model, Org Design & Workforce Benchmarking</p></div>
    <div><p class="k">Industry</p><p class="v">Energy & Utilities</p></div>
    <div><p class="k">Support Needed</p><p class="v">Organizational Benchmarking & Operating Model Consultant</p></div>
    <div><p class="k">Duration</p><p class="v">12 Weeks</p></div>
  </div>

  <h2>The Challenge</h2>
  <p>A leading U.S. energy utility wanted to assess whether its supply chain organization was structured appropriately to support current spend and future growth. Leadership needed clarity on:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>How the organization compared with peers on spend supported per FTE.</li>
    <li>How roles were distributed across sourcing, procurement operations, PMO/CoE, and planning.</li>
    <li>Whether the current structure could sustain governance and execution as spend scaled.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The objective was to create a fact base for workforce planning and operating model decisions.</p>

  <h2>My Role</h2>
  <p>I led the benchmarking assessment across supply chain structure, role allocation, and functional capacity. My responsibilities included defining the benchmarking approach and peer comparison framework; assessing spend supported per FTE across the organization; reviewing sourcing, procurement operations, PMO/CoE, and planning coverage; and translating findings into executive-level structural implications.</p>

  <h2>The Approach</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Benchmark the structure</strong> — compared supply chain sizing against peer utilities using spend supported per FTE.</li>
    <li><strong>Map role allocation</strong> — reviewed how category managers, sourcing specialists, procurement ops, and PMO/CoE roles were deployed.</li>
    <li><strong>Test functional coverage</strong> — assessed where execution, governance, and planning responsibilities sat.</li>
    <li><strong>Define scale implications</strong> — identified the structural reinforcement required as spend increased.</li>
  </ol>

